  87 class DummySpinner(object):
  88     def __init__(self, text="", **kwargs):
  89         # type: (str, Any) -> None
  90         if DISABLE_COLORS:
  91             colorama.init()
  92         self.text = to_native_string(decode_output(text)) if text else ""
  93         self.stdout = kwargs.get("stdout", sys.stdout)
  94         self.stderr = kwargs.get("stderr", sys.stderr)
  95         self.out_buff = StringIO()
  96         self.write_to_stdout = kwargs.get("write_to_stdout", False)
  97         super(DummySpinner, self).__init__()
  98 
  99     def __enter__(self):
 100         if self.text and self.text != "None":
 101             if self.write_to_stdout:
 102                 self.write(self.text)
 103         return self
 104 
 105     def __exit__(self, exc_type, exc_val, tb):
 106         if exc_type:
 107             import traceback
 108 
 109             formatted_tb = traceback.format_exception(exc_type, exc_val, tb)
 110             self.write_err("".join(formatted_tb))
 111         self._close_output_buffer()
 112         return False
 113 
 114     def __getattr__(self, k):  # pragma: no cover
 115         try:
 116             retval = super(DummySpinner, self).__getattribute__(k)
 117         except AttributeError:
 118             if k in COLOR_MAP.keys() or k.upper() in COLORS:
 119                 return self
 120             raise
 121         else:
 122             return retval
 123 
 124     def _close_output_buffer(self):
 125         if self.out_buff and not self.out_buff.closed:
 126             try:
 127                 self.out_buff.close()
 128             except Exception:
 129                 pass
 130 
 131     def fail(self, exitcode=1, text="FAIL"):
 132         # type: (int, str) -> None
 133         if text is not None and text != "None":
 134             if self.write_to_stdout:
 135                 self.write(text)
 136             else:
 137                 self.write_err(text)
 138         self._close_output_buffer()
 139 
 140     def ok(self, text="OK"):
 141         # type: (str) -> int
 142         if text is not None and text != "None":
 143             if self.write_to_stdout:
 144                 self.write(text)
 145             else:
 146                 self.write_err(text)
 147         self._close_output_buffer()
 148         return 0
 149 
 150     def hide_and_write(self, text, target=None):
 151         # type: (str, Optional[str]) -> None
 152         if not target:
 153             target = self.stdout
 154         if text is None or isinstance(text, six.string_types) and text == "None":
 155             pass
 156         target.write(decode_output(u"\r", target_stream=target))
 157         self._hide_cursor(target=target)
 158         target.write(decode_output(u"{0}\n".format(text), target_stream=target))
 159         target.write(CLEAR_LINE)
 160         self._show_cursor(target=target)
 161 
 162     def write(self, text=None):
 163         # type: (Optional[str]) -> None
 164         if not self.write_to_stdout:
 165             return self.write_err(text)
 166         if text is None or isinstance(text, six.string_types) and text == "None":
 167             pass
 168         if not self.stdout.closed:
 169             stdout = self.stdout
 170         else:
 171             stdout = sys.stdout
 172         stdout.write(decode_output(u"\r", target_stream=stdout))
 173         text = to_text(text)
 174         line = decode_output(u"{0}\n".format(text), target_stream=stdout)
 175         stdout.write(line)
 176         stdout.write(CLEAR_LINE)
 177 
 178     def write_err(self, text=None):
 179         # type: (Optional[str]) -> None
 180         if text is None or isinstance(text, six.string_types) and text == "None":
 181             pass
 182         text = to_text(text)
 183         if not self.stderr.closed:
 184             stderr = self.stderr
 185         else:
 186             if sys.stderr.closed:
 187                 print(text)
 188                 return
 189             stderr = sys.stderr
 190         stderr.write(decode_output(u"\r", target_stream=stderr))
 191         line = decode_output(u"{0}\n".format(text), target_stream=stderr)
 192         stderr.write(line)
 193         stderr.write(CLEAR_LINE)
 194 
 195     @staticmethod
 196     def _hide_cursor(target=None):
 197         # type: (Optional[IO]) -> None
 198         pass
 199 
 200     @staticmethod
 201     def _show_cursor(target=None):
 202         # type: (Optional[IO]) -> None
 203         pass

 210 class VistirSpinner(SpinBase):
 211     "A spinner class for handling spinners on windows and posix."
 212 
 213     def __init__(self, *args, **kwargs):
 214         # type: (Any, Any)
 215         """
 216         Get a spinner object or a dummy spinner to wrap a context.
 217 
 218         Keyword Arguments:
 219         :param str spinner_name: A spinner type e.g. "dots" or "bouncingBar" (default: {"bouncingBar"})
 220         :param str start_text: Text to start off the spinner with (default: {None})
 221         :param dict handler_map: Handler map for signals to be handled gracefully (default: {None})
 222         :param bool nospin: If true, use the dummy spinner (default: {False})
 223         :param bool write_to_stdout: Writes to stdout if true, otherwise writes to stderr (default: True)
 224         """
 225 
 226         self.handler = handler
 227         colorama.init()
 228         sigmap = {}  # type: TSignalMap
 229         if handler:
 230             sigmap.update({signal.SIGINT: handler, signal.SIGTERM: handler})
 231         handler_map = kwargs.pop("handler_map", {})
 232         if os.name == "nt":
 233             sigmap[signal.SIGBREAK] = handler
 234         else:
 235             sigmap[signal.SIGALRM] = handler
 236         if handler_map:
 237             sigmap.update(handler_map)
 238         spinner_name = kwargs.pop("spinner_name", "bouncingBar")
 239         start_text = kwargs.pop("start_text", None)
 240         _text = kwargs.pop("text", "Running...")
 241         kwargs["text"] = start_text if start_text is not None else _text
 242         kwargs["sigmap"] = sigmap
 243         kwargs["spinner"] = getattr(Spinners, spinner_name, "")
 244         write_to_stdout = kwargs.pop("write_to_stdout", True)
 245         self.stdout = kwargs.pop("stdout", sys.stdout)
 246         self.stderr = kwargs.pop("stderr", sys.stderr)
 247         self.out_buff = StringIO()
 248         self.write_to_stdout = write_to_stdout
 249         self.is_dummy = bool(yaspin is None)
 250         self._stop_spin = None  # type: Optional[threading.Event]
 251         self._hide_spin = None  # type: Optional[threading.Event]
 252         self._spin_thread = None  # type: Optional[threading.Thread]
 253         super(VistirSpinner, self).__init__(*args, **kwargs)
 254         if DISABLE_COLORS:
 255             colorama.deinit()
 256 
 257     def ok(self, text=u"OK", err=False):
 258         # type: (str, bool) -> None
 259         """Set Ok (success) finalizer to a spinner."""
 260         # Do not display spin text for ok state
 261         self._text = None
 262 
 263         _text = to_text(text) if text else u"OK"
 264         err = err or not self.write_to_stdout
 265         self._freeze(_text, err=err)
 266 
 267     def fail(self, text=u"FAIL", err=False):
 268         # type: (str, bool) -> None
 269         """Set fail finalizer to a spinner."""
 270         # Do not display spin text for fail state
 271         self._text = None
 272 
 273         _text = text if text else u"FAIL"
 274         err = err or not self.write_to_stdout
 275         self._freeze(_text, err=err)
 276 
 277     def hide_and_write(self, text, target=None):
 278         # type: (str, Optional[str]) -> None
 279         if not target:
 280             target = self.stdout
 281         if text is None or isinstance(text, six.string_types) and text == u"None":
 282             pass
 283         target.write(decode_output(u"\r"))
 284         self._hide_cursor(target=target)
 285         target.write(decode_output(u"{0}\n".format(text)))
 286         target.write(CLEAR_LINE)
 287         self._show_cursor(target=target)
 288 
 289     def write(self, text):  # pragma: no cover
 290         # type: (str) -> None
 291         if not self.write_to_stdout:
 292             return self.write_err(text)
 293         stdout = self.stdout
 294         if self.stdout.closed:
 295             stdout = sys.stdout
 296         stdout.write(decode_output(u"\r", target_stream=stdout))
 297         stdout.write(decode_output(CLEAR_LINE, target_stream=stdout))
 298         if text is None:
 299             text = ""
 300         text = decode_output(u"{0}\n".format(text), target_stream=stdout)
 301         stdout.write(text)
 302         self.out_buff.write(text)
 303 
 304     def write_err(self, text):  # pragma: no cover
 305         # type: (str) -> None
 306         """Write error text in the terminal without breaking the spinner."""
 307         stderr = self.stderr
 308         if self.stderr.closed:
 309             stderr = sys.stderr
 310         stderr.write(decode_output(u"\r", target_stream=stderr))
 311         stderr.write(decode_output(CLEAR_LINE, target_stream=stderr))
 312         if text is None:
 313             text = ""
 314         text = decode_output(u"{0}\n".format(text), target_stream=stderr)
 315         self.stderr.write(text)
 316         self.out_buff.write(decode_output(text, target_stream=self.out_buff))
 317 
 318     def start(self):
 319         # type: () -> None
 320         if self._sigmap:
 321             self._register_signal_handlers()
 322 
 323         target = self.stdout if self.write_to_stdout else self.stderr
 324         if target.isatty():
 325             self._hide_cursor(target=target)
 326 
 327         self._stop_spin = threading.Event()
 328         self._hide_spin = threading.Event()
 329         self._spin_thread = threading.Thread(target=self._spin)
 330         self._spin_thread.start()
 331 
 332     def stop(self):
 333         # type: () -> None
 334         if self._dfl_sigmap:
 335             # Reset registered signal handlers to default ones
 336             self._reset_signal_handlers()
 337 
 338         if self._spin_thread:
 339             self._stop_spin.set()
 340             self._spin_thread.join()
 341 
 342         target = self.stdout if self.write_to_stdout else self.stderr
 343         if target.isatty():
 344             target.write("\r")
 345 
 346         if self.write_to_stdout:
 347             self._clear_line()
 348         else:
 349             self._clear_err()
 350 
 351         if target.isatty():
 352             self._show_cursor(target=target)
 353         self.out_buff.close()
 354 
 355     def _freeze(self, final_text, err=False):
 356         # type: (str, bool) -> None
 357         """Stop spinner, compose last frame and 'freeze' it."""
 358         if not final_text:
 359             final_text = ""
 360         target = self.stderr if err else self.stdout
 361         if target.closed:
 362             target = sys.stderr if err else sys.stdout
 363         text = to_text(final_text)
 364         last_frame = self._compose_out(text, mode="last")
 365         self._last_frame = decode_output(last_frame, target_stream=target)
 366 
 367         # Should be stopped here, otherwise prints after
 368         # self._freeze call will mess up the spinner
 369         self.stop()
 370         target.write(self._last_frame)
 371 
 372     def _compose_color_func(self):
 373         # type: () -> Callable[..., str]
 374         fn = functools.partial(
 375             colored, color=self._color, on_color=self._on_color, attrs=list(self._attrs)
 376         )
 377         return fn
 378 
 379     def _compose_out(self, frame, mode=None):
 380         # type: (str, Optional[str]) -> Text
 381         # Ensure Unicode input
 382 
 383         frame = to_text(frame)
 384         if self._text is None:
 385             self._text = u""
 386         text = to_text(self._text)
 387         if self._color_func is not None:
 388             frame = self._color_func(frame)
 389         if self._side == "right":
 390             frame, text = text, frame
 391         # Mode
 392         frame = to_text(frame)
 393         if not mode:
 394             out = u"\r{0} {1}".format(frame, text)
 395         else:
 396             out = u"{0} {1}\n".format(frame, text)
 397         return out
 398 
 399     def _spin(self):
 400         # type: () -> None
 401         target = self.stdout if self.write_to_stdout else self.stderr
 402         clear_fn = self._clear_line if self.write_to_stdout else self._clear_err
 403         while not self._stop_spin.is_set():
 404 
 405             if self._hide_spin.is_set():
 406                 # Wait a bit to avoid wasting cycles
 407                 time.sleep(self._interval)
 408                 continue
 409 
 410             # Compose output
 411             spin_phase = next(self._cycle)
 412             out = self._compose_out(spin_phase)
 413             out = decode_output(out, target)
 414 
 415             # Write
 416             target.write(out)
 417             clear_fn()
 418             target.flush()
 419 
 420             # Wait
 421             time.sleep(self._interval)
 422             target.write("\b")
 423 
 424     def _register_signal_handlers(self):
 425         # type: () -> None
 426         # SIGKILL cannot be caught or ignored, and the receiving
 427         # process cannot perform any clean-up upon receiving this
 428         # signal.
 429         try:
 430             if signal.SIGKILL in self._sigmap.keys():
 431                 raise ValueError(
 432                     "Trying to set handler for SIGKILL signal. "
 433                     "SIGKILL cannot be cought or ignored in POSIX systems."
 434                 )
 435         except AttributeError:
 436             pass
 437 
 438         for sig, sig_handler in self._sigmap.items():
 439             # A handler for a particular signal, once set, remains
 440             # installed until it is explicitly reset. Store default
 441             # signal handlers for subsequent reset at cleanup phase.
 442             dfl_handler = signal.getsignal(sig)
 443             self._dfl_sigmap[sig] = dfl_handler
 444 
 445             # ``signal.SIG_DFL`` and ``signal.SIG_IGN`` are also valid
 446             # signal handlers and are not callables.
 447             if callable(sig_handler):
 448                 # ``signal.signal`` accepts handler function which is
 449                 # called with two arguments: signal number and the
 450                 # interrupted stack frame. ``functools.partial`` solves
 451                 # the problem of passing spinner instance into the handler
 452                 # function.
 453                 sig_handler = functools.partial(sig_handler, spinner=self)
 454 
 455             signal.signal(sig, sig_handler)
 456 
 457     def _reset_signal_handlers(self):
 458         # type: () -> None
 459         for sig, sig_handler in self._dfl_sigmap.items():
 460             signal.signal(sig, sig_handler)
 461 
 462     @staticmethod
 463     def _hide_cursor(target=None):
 464         # type: (Optional[IO]) -> None
 465         if not target:
 466             target = sys.stdout
 467         hide_cursor(stream=target)
 468 
 469     @staticmethod
 470     def _show_cursor(target=None):
 471         # type: (Optional[IO]) -> None
 472         if not target:
 473             target = sys.stdout
 474         show_cursor(stream=target)
 475 
 476     @staticmethod
 477     def _clear_err():
 478         # type: () -> None
 479         sys.stderr.write(CLEAR_LINE)
 480 
 481     @staticmethod
 482     def _clear_line():
 483         # type: () -> None
 484         sys.stdout.write(CLEAR_LINE)

 487 def create_spinner(*args, **kwargs):
 488     # type: (Any, Any) -> Union[DummySpinner, VistirSpinner]
 489     nospin = kwargs.pop("nospin", False)
 490     use_yaspin = kwargs.pop("use_yaspin", not nospin)
 491     if nospin or not use_yaspin:
 492         return DummySpinner(*args, **kwargs)
 493     return VistirSpinner(*args, **kwargs)
